WEBVTT

00:10.637 --> 00:12.972
Do you know who he is?

00:16.768 --> 00:18.520
Who he really is?

00:21.690 --> 00:24.150
Shadow Moon...

00:24.317 --> 00:26.319
You're my man now.

00:26.486 --> 00:28.279
You've gotten yourself
mixed up

00:28.446 --> 00:30.156
in some really weird shit,
Shadow.

00:30.323 --> 00:32.867
You shouldn't
trust him. Grimnir. Don't trust him.

00:33.034 --> 00:35.704
Trying to start a war,
Glad-O-War?

00:35.870 --> 00:38.498
We're at war already
and we're losing.

00:38.665 --> 00:40.250
Who are you?

00:40.417 --> 00:42.669
You wouldn't
believe me if I told you.

00:45.797 --> 00:47.173
What should I believe?

00:47.340 --> 00:49.884
- What's today?
- Wednesday.

00:50.051 --> 00:52.429
Today's my day.

03:32.213 --> 03:34.132
This is all too big.

03:34.299 --> 03:36.759
Too much going on at once.

03:39.721 --> 03:41.598
We should start with a story.

03:41.764 --> 03:43.224
Oh, Jesus, Nancy!

03:43.391 --> 03:44.809
I'm gonna tell you a story.

03:44.976 --> 03:48.104
Haven't got time for a story.
Just do the fucking work, huh?

03:48.271 --> 03:50.607
Let me tell
a goddamned story!

03:51.649 --> 03:53.776
I got a good one.

03:54.819 --> 03:56.529
Real good.

03:56.696 --> 03:58.865
Once upon a time...

03:59.032 --> 04:01.659
See? It sounds good already.

04:01.826 --> 04:03.202
You're hooked.

04:03.369 --> 04:05.204
Just get on with it, huh?

04:08.416 --> 04:09.876
Once upon a time,

04:10.043 --> 04:11.586
there was a fucking queen.

04:12.629 --> 04:14.172
She had it all,

04:14.339 --> 04:16.841
the glory, the power.

04:17.008 --> 04:20.970
Worshippers, eager to give
and grateful to receive.

04:21.137 --> 04:23.139
Why?

04:23.306 --> 04:26.267
Because she had the gift
of the gift.

04:26.434 --> 04:30.188
The blessing of blessings,
hers to bestow.

04:31.481 --> 04:33.483
And her place of worship?

04:35.735 --> 04:37.695
Well, that was the place to be.

04:38.738 --> 04:41.240
THAT was the goddamn shit.

05:30.540 --> 05:33.376
It was
good fucking times.

06:09.787 --> 06:12.248
Kings didn't like that.

06:12.415 --> 06:14.542
Kings came one after the other

06:14.709 --> 06:17.003
to knock her off her throne.

06:18.421 --> 06:20.590
They didn't last long.

07:37.458 --> 07:40.169
When the queen
was done with you...

07:41.212 --> 07:43.381
..you were gone.

07:43.548 --> 07:45.716
Worse ways to go.

08:30.845 --> 08:34.182
Clothes and hair
change with the times,

08:34.348 --> 08:35.975
but this queen...

08:37.768 --> 08:40.021
..she kept the party going.

09:14.096 --> 09:18.935
♪ As a friend
Not as a fighter

09:21.229 --> 09:26.400
♪ I come as someone you invited

09:27.610 --> 09:30.821
♪ You seem to confess

09:31.864 --> 09:34.951
♪ It's all so senseless

09:38.746 --> 09:40.539
♪ Ah

09:40.706 --> 09:42.625
♪ Oh

09:42.792 --> 09:44.335
♪ Ah. ♪

09:49.423 --> 09:51.550
But the kings,

09:51.717 --> 09:54.804
they kept coming after her.

09:56.013 --> 09:58.724
Our queen's power,

09:58.891 --> 10:01.519
which is the power
of all women,

10:01.686 --> 10:05.606
the power of rebirth
and creation.

10:07.817 --> 10:11.153
It makes some men kneel in awe

10:11.320 --> 10:12.947
and give gifts.

10:13.114 --> 10:16.242
But it makes other men angry.

10:20.037 --> 10:21.706
And you know it -

10:21.872 --> 10:25.710
anger gets shit done.

10:28.087 --> 10:29.588
So men did what they do.

10:29.755 --> 10:34.176
They took from her that power.
Took them a long time.

10:34.343 --> 10:38.597
Took them guns and knives
and sharp dicks.

10:38.764 --> 10:40.808
But they grabbed the power

10:40.975 --> 10:43.394
they were too scared
for a queen to have.

10:49.442 --> 10:51.027
They laundered it

10:51.193 --> 10:53.779
and gave it to men.

10:53.946 --> 10:58.534
They forced our queen
into the back seat.

10:59.577 --> 11:01.871
<i>The remaining flight time</i>

11:02.038 --> 11:04.540
<i>to New York's John F. Kennedy Airport
is 11 hours.</i>

11:04.707 --> 11:06.542
<i>So sit back, relax and enjoy...</i>

11:06.709 --> 11:08.711
"Where is the library?"

11:09.754 --> 11:11.422
"Where is the library?"

